Task.Name: Home Move
Five to Eight Weeks Before Moving
Planning the Move
Task.Notes: This section prepares you to plan your move based on your timetable and moving requirements.

Task.Name: Calculate moving expenses
Task.Notes: Expenses may include supplies, movers, rental truck, and deposits and fees for setting up a new residence.

Task.Name: Determine the best method of moving
Task.Notes: Moving methods may include hiring moving services, doing it yourself, or combining approaches.

Task.Name: Create a moving-expense receipt file
Create a moving binder
Task.Notes: Create a binder to store moving plan, important move documentation, and a log of move notes and activities.

Task.Name: Household Administration
Task.Notes: Household administration includes all activities that are required to transfer a household from location to another aside from moving physical items.

Task.Name: Finances and Insurance
Task.Notes: Tasks related to finances and insurance include all changes to banking activity, insurance, and costs of the move.

Task.Name: Review household finances
Verify that your belongings are insured for the move
Task.Notes: Your homeowner or renter's insurance may cover your belongings. Standard insurance coverage from a moving service rarely covers your belongings for replacement value.

Task.Name: Appraise valuables specifically insured for the move
Transfer insurance policies to your new address
Task.Notes: Instruct your insurance agent to transfer property, fire, and auto insurance.

Task.Name: Transfer medical insurance to your new location
Task.Notes: Inform your company's benefit representative of your new address. If you're changing jobs, verify that you are receiving interim health insurance.

Task.Name: Notifications
Task.Notes: Notifications include notifying friends, family, government agencies, magazines you subscribe to, or others who need your new address.

Task.Name: Notify your employer of your moving dates and new address
Transfer, sell, or discontinue any memberships
Task.Notes: Memberships may include clubs, gyms, organizations, or community groups.

Task.Name: Vital Services and Records
Task.Notes: Vital services may include medical, schools, and veterinary care.

Task.Name: Organize important records
Task.Notes: Important records may include prescriptions, optical prescriptions, x-rays, medical and dental records, school records, and birth certificates.

Task.Name: Contact your doctor, dentist, and vet for referrals
Request additional refills of vital medications
Your New Residence
Task.Notes: Your New Residence includes all activities that will help you get accustomed to your new community or set up your new residence. These activities also include establishing utilities and government services.

Task.Name: Collect shopping and dining guides from your new community
Determine the location of the police, fire department and hospitals
Change drivers/vehicle license address if required
Place orders for new furniture
Moving
Task.Notes: Moving encompasses all activities involved in physically moving your possessions from one location to another.

Task.Name: Movers
Task.Notes: Movers refers to all activities done by or in conjunction with a moving service.

Task.Name: Obtain estimates from several moving services
Task.Notes: On-site estimates tend to be more accurate and save you from surprises when the movers arrive.

Task.Name: Request references from each moving service
Select moving service
Discuss rough details with movers
Task.Notes: Rough details may include costs, packing requirements, preliminary move dates, and insurance availability.

Task.Name: Packing
Task.Notes: Packing includes all activities in preparing and packing your possessions to be moved.

Task.Name: Inventory and organize all possessions
Task.Notes: It is important to decide which possessions will be moved by movers, moved by you, or donated and sold. You should move valuable or irreplaceable items such as legal documents, jewelry, photos, or home videos yourself.

Task.Name: Begin using food and cleaning supplies currently on hand
Task.Notes: Avoid shopping for anything you'll have to move.

Task.Name: Start cleaning closets, bookcases, and other storage areas
Conduct a sale or donate to charity
Decide what furniture items you want to keep
Task.Notes: Obtain a floor plan of your new residence if possible.

Task.Name: Reserve storage if necessary
Preparing for Moving Day
Task.Notes: Preparing for moving day refers to all activities that will need to be done on the day of the move.

Task.Name: Make any long distance travel arrangements
Task.Notes: Arrangements may include airlines, hotels, or car rental. Make sure to make arrangements for your pets.

Task.Name: Three to Five Weeks Before Moving
Household Administration
Finances and Insurance
Research and choose bank at the new location
Open new bank account
Order bank checks with your new address
Close any local charge accounts
Notifications
Schedule disconnection of utilities
Task.Notes: Utilities to disconnect may include the following: - Water company - Cable TV company - Electric company - Newspaper delivery - Gas/oil company - Dairy delivery - Telephone company Be sure to specify that the final day of service is on (for deliveries such as newspaper or dairy products) or after the move date (utilities).

Task.Name: Change your address with government agencies if required
Clear up any unpaid taxes or parking tickets
Task.Notes: Contact your local government. These fees may follow you to your new residence.

Task.Name: Transfer car registration to your new location
Vital Services and Records
Register your children in their new schools
Forward children's school records to the new school district
Your New Residence
Order mailing labels with your new address
Determine if there are pet requirements at the new location
Schedule move with the building management at the new location
Task.Notes: Move-in times may be limited. Elevators may need to be scheduled.

Task.Name: Schedule cable television installation if required
Schedule internet installation if required
Contact utility companies and sign up for new service
Task.Notes: Schedule utility connection before your move-in date for: - Water company - Electric company - Gas/oil company - Telephone company

Task.Name: Moving
Movers
Confirm your move date with your moving service
Do-It-Yourself
Task.Notes: Do-it-yourself refers to tasks you need to complete if you are making the move on your own or if you are doing any part of the move.

Task.Name: Reserve a truck or trailer
Begin enlisting assistance for moving day
Packing
Start collecting boxes, tape, and padding
Arrange for disposal of items not sold or donated
Begin letting children do some of their own packing and labeling
Begin packing books, seasonal clothing, or sporting equipment
Send furniture, drapes, and carpets for repair or cleaning
Have appliances serviced for moving, if applicable
Preparing for Moving Day
Arrange for child care the day of the move
Task.Notes: A friend or sitter can keep children safe during the loading and unloading process.

Task.Name: One to Two Weeks Before Moving
Household Administration
Finances and Insurance
Transfer your bank accounts to new bank or new location
Close existing bank accounts at old location
Empty safe-deposit box
Organize appliance documents
Task.Notes: Documents could include warranties, instruction manuals, and receipts.

Task.Name: Make arrangements to pay for your move
Buy traveler's checks
Notifications
Fill out mail change of address cards
Distribute new address
Task.Notes: Provide your new address for your - Charge accounts - Credit cards - Loan companies - Subscriptions - Insurance agency - Friends, relatives

Task.Name: If no longer required, cancel local deliveries
Cancel newspaper delivery
Take trash to dump or recycling center
Coordinate with friend to act as your message center
Vital Services and Records
Task.Notes: Vital services may include medical professionals, schools, and veterinary care.

Task.Name: Have medical and dental records forwarded
Contact your pharmacist for referral
Transfer your prescriptions to this new pharmacy
Your New Residence
Contact previous residents for appliance documentation
Subscribe to the local newspapers and community newsletters
Moving
Movers
Check with mover about moving house plants
Task.Notes: Some movers will not move plants. It is illegal for mover to move house plants in some locations.

Task.Name: Obtain moving service contact numbers
Acquire labels for boxes (for example, Fragile, Load First, Load Last)
Verify that the moving service has your contact numbers
Task.Notes: Contact numbers should include the lodging numbers if you don't go directly to your new location.

Task.Name: Give moving service written directions to the new location
Do-It-Yourself
Move possessions to storage facility if necessary
Confirm assistance for moving day
Verify dolly available with truck rental
Packing
Clean appliances
Pick up all dry cleaning
Pack items that you do not use regularly
Task.Notes: These items can include clothing, books, pots, pans, and kitchenware. Be sure to label all boxes.

Task.Name: Pack all valuables to move personally
Locate hazardous waste disposal sites
Drain all fluids from your lawn mower and power tools
Dispose of all hazardous household materials
Task.Notes: Hazardous materials include cleaning fluids, lighter fluid, and aerosols.

Task.Name: Have mover pack your goods (unless doing it yourself)
Pack travel bags and confirm travel arrangements
Preparing for Move Day
Have your automobile serviced if you're traveling by car
Plan auto route
Plan meals that will use up the food in your freezer
Empty, defrost, and clean refrigerator and freezer
Prepare a survival kit for move day
Task.Notes: Your survival kit may include snacks, beverages, and children's games for the trip.

Task.Name: Prepare your pet's survival kit
Task.Notes: Your pet may need food, water bowl, toys, and bedding.

Task.Name: Prepare an immediate-need kit for move day
Task.Notes: You may need items such as the following: - Telephone - Light bulbs - Tool kit - Scissors - Flashlight - Large trash bags - Paper towels - Toilet paper - Linens to make your beds

Task.Name: Day of the Move
Old Residence
Moving
Have tools, tape, twine, and spare boxes on hand
Be present throughout the entire move
Verify all possessions have been packed and loaded
Task.Notes: Verify that everything is packed and loaded before the moving service leaves the premises.

Task.Name: Make sure fragile items are handled carefully
Pack cleaning supplies including a vacuum cleaner in a box labeled Last Load
Verify that bedding gets packed last
New Residence
Household Administration
Empty, defrost, and clean the new refrigerator
Designate a room for your pet
Have snacks and beverages on hand throughout the day
Moving
Be present throughout the entire move
Task.Notes: If you can't be present yourself, designate another adult to be present with the moving service.

Task.Name: Make sure fragile items are handled carefully
Review all paperwork when the moving service arrives
Pay moving service before unpacking
Check carefully for any damaged or missing items
Read and sign bill of lading
Retain copies of the bill of lading and inventory
Move completed
One to Two Weeks After the Move
Household Administration
Finances and Insurance
Put valuables into a safety deposit box in the new bank
Notifications
Arrange for new registration of cars (bicycles also, if required)
Have pets licensed
Change your voter registration, if required
Vital Services and Records
Contact new dentists and doctors to verify record delivery
Get recommendations for babysitters, nanny agencies, and other services
Verify that new schools have received records
Update driver's license and car license plates
Your New Residence
Make additional sets of keys and change locks if necessary
Ask for repair service recommendations
Meet your neighbors (write down their names)
Find out about recycling at the new location
Enjoy your new home
